article.headline: Northeastern 76, New Hampshire 69
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea scored 21 points and dished out nine assists and Javorie Wilson added 19 points and 11 rebounds to lead Northeastern over New Hampshire 76-69 Saturday. Northeastern (13-8, 7-3 America East) has won five of its last seven games. Blagoj Janev led New Hampshire (5-15, 1-9) with 17 points, 15 in the first half. The Huskies almost came unraveled with 16 minutes left in the second half as Barea and Wilson exchanged heated words after Barea airballed a 3-pointer from 25 feet away. Coach Ron Everhart was forced to call two timeouts in the next 3:40 to try to calm down his team, and Wilson and Barea responded by hitting two 3-pointers each in the following 2:06 to give Northeastern a 63-54 lead with 9:14 left. The Wildcats got as close as 65-61 with 3:09 left, but Wilson buried a 3-pointer on Northeastern's next possession to put the Huskies ahead by seven. After trailing by as much as 18-5, New Hampshire rallied to take its first and only lead, 39-38, with 1:46 left in the first half as Craig Walls capped a 7-0 run with a free throw. The Huskies responded by closing out the half on a 7-0 run of their own, and Bennett Davis' basket with one second left gave Northeastern a 45-39 lead at the break.
